    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-04-08T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-04-08T08:30:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <head>13. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Iran</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d13fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL 23–9 IRAN. Confidential. Repeated to Baghdad and Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-04-08T17:00:00+03:30">April 8, 1964, 5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>890. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 882.<note n="2" xml:id="d13fn2">
                        <ref target="#d12">Document 12</ref>.</note> Further background on release
                    of <persName corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName>, obtained from Prime
                    Minister: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Govt made clear to <persName corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName>
                            that if he engages in political activities, he will be re-arrested.
                            Khomeini allegedly promised behave.</item>
                        <pb facs="0055" n="27" xml:id="pg_27"/>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_MHA1">Mansur</persName> allowed it to be
                            understood he had had difficulty persuading Shah that <persName
                                corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName> should be freed.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> felt it was desirable free <persName
                                corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName> now, rather than just before
                            Moharam, because later release might be interpreted as due to fear of
                            rioting similar to last year’s.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Govt has “taken steps” with other leading mullahs, notably Milani,
                            Qomi and Shariat-Madari, to prevent <persName corresp="#p_KAR1"
                                >Khomeini</persName>’s position being strengthened as result his
                            release.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HJC2">Holmes</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
